<item>
            <title>[SWF-973] MessageContextErrors ignores nestedPath in getFieldValue</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SWF-973</link>
                <project id="10050" key="SWF">Spring Web Flow</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Implementation of MessageContextErrors.getFieldValue causes error when a validator calls errors.getFieldValue (e.g. by calling ValidationUtils.rejectIfEmptyOrWhitespace) after calling errors.pushNestedPath. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This applies to MessageContextErrors that are initialized with &lt;br/&gt;
mappingResults = null&lt;br/&gt;
expressionParser = DefaultExpressionParserFactory.getExpressionParser()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason for the error seems to be that getFieldValue calls parseFieldExpression(field) ignoring the nestedPath.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, in spring-faces, the FlowActionListener initializes a MessageContextErrors with&lt;br/&gt;
mappingResults = null&lt;br/&gt;
expressionParser = null&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and getFieldValue is therefore unavailable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See forum thread: &lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=63958&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=63958&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
